# Frontend & App Rules

## Architecture
- Static-first; no backend/data layer unless explicitly required.
- Pages/layouts in `src/app/`; components when extracted; styling via Tailwind or `globals.css` tokens.
- Avoid premature abstractions; incremental edits over broad rewrites.
- Preserve existing patterns before introducing new ones.

## Next.js
- App Router under `src/app/`.
- Metadata in `layout.tsx` or route-level exports.
- Use `next/image` for local images with meaningful `alt`.

## TypeScript & React
- `strict: true`; avoid `any` unless justified.
- Functional components; split files that become hard to review.

## Styling
- Tailwind utilities for local styling; shared tokens in `globals.css`.
- Prefer classes/tokens over inline styles when equivalent.

## Content & accessibility
- Preserve Portuguese user-facing text unless asked to change.
- Semantic HTML (`main`, logical heading order).
- Maintain contrast and readability after style changes.

## Do not
- One-shot full page/app rewrites.
- New libraries for small styling/content tasks.
- Disable lint/type checks to fix issues.
- Bulk rename/move without explicit request.
